<item>
 <title>Mahabharata resources!</title>
 <link>http://www.srichinmoycentre.org/node/14082</link>
 <description>
    &lt;blockquote&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;krishnaandarjuna-300x211.jpg&quot; class=&quot;left&quot; src=&quot;http://aum.vasudevaserver.netdna-cdn.com/cdn/farfuture/heyQFAioDYM7OabCJS3uO-zX0nhumfBz7gBy-emUMqE/mtime:1379710950/files/Members/patanga/krishnaandarjuna-300x211.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width:300px; height:211px&quot; /&gt;The Mahabharata&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Is&lt;br /&gt;
		The Reality&amp;#39;s body.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.srichinmoylibrary.com/message-light-of-the-bhagavad-gita&quot;&gt;Sri Chinmoy, &lt;em&gt;The Message-Light Of The Bhagavad Gita&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Agni Press, 1999&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have loved and still love to read, listen and watch the Mahabharata. It inspires me spiritually so much that I have made a compilation of resourses on it to share with you. Here you will see songs, stories, TV series, audiobooks, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Sri Chinmoy&amp;#39;s Commentaries on the Vedas, Upanishads and Bhagavad Gita&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.amazon.com/Commentaries-Vedas-Upanishads-Bhagavad-Gita/dp/0884971139&quot;&gt;http://www.amazon.com/Commentaries-Vedas-Upanishads-Bhagavad-Gita/dp/0884971139&lt;/a&gt;. Excellent!!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	B.R. Chopra&amp;rsquo;s Mahabharata TV series (94 episodes)&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=05uPstPKz04&quot;&gt;Episode 1 starts here&lt;/a&gt;, from there you get the rest. It is EXTREMELY nice. It takes a few episodes to really get into it, but then you&amp;acute;ll want to see all 94 episodes!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Mahabharata audiobook&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://mahabharatapodcast.blogspot.com&quot;&gt;Free by Lawrence Manzo. &lt;/a&gt;It is based on a complete version.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Mahabharata Comics&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.amazon.com/Mahabharata-Bhagavad-Mythology-Children-religious/dp/8190599011&quot;&gt;Amar Chitra Katha. &lt;/a&gt;Condensed version&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Mahabharata condensed version&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.amazon.com/The-Mahabharata-Penguin-Classics-Anonymous/dp/0140446818&quot;&gt;Penguin Classics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Sri Chinmoy Sings the Bhagavad Gita&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.radiosrichinmoy.org/369/dream-boat-passages-from-the-bhagavad-gita/&quot;&gt;http://www.radiosrichinmoy.org/369/dream-boat-passages-from-the-bhagavad-gita/ &lt;/a&gt;Sri Chinmoy recites and sings many passages from the Bhagavad Gita.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;
	Sri Chinmoy&amp;rsquo;s Songs on the Heroes of the Mahabharata&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.srichinmoysongs.com/song/view/kbsm-arjuner-gurudev-sanatan/9233/&quot;&gt;http://www.srichinmoysongs.com/song/view/kbsm-arjuner-gurudev-sanatan/9233/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
