<item>
 <title>Dead Man&#039;s Road   (poem/gedicht)</title>
 <link>http://www.srichinmoycentre.org/node/12633</link>
 <description>
    &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The blue trees sway on dead man&amp;rsquo;s road&lt;br /&gt;
	Where the tired souls walk freely and proud&lt;br /&gt;
	Blue trees that sway singing hymns of praise&lt;br /&gt;
	Under a golden welkin shot with pearly cloud.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The tired souls with wreaths of emerald green&lt;br /&gt;
	After the war was fought on fields of clashing noise&lt;br /&gt;
	The tired souls with star-specked eyes and wreaths of emerald green&lt;br /&gt;
	At war&amp;rsquo;s end, in the hush of glory&amp;rsquo;s poise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The weary souls that march towards the gates of Time&lt;br /&gt;
	Much they have seen, much more remains to see &amp;ndash;&lt;br /&gt;
	Wisdom like a shield of ivory sits upon their brow&lt;br /&gt;
	As they cross the marbled doorstep of Eternity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Still walking proud on dead man&amp;rsquo;s road.&lt;br /&gt;
	All is silent now with the rapture of an ancient dream,&lt;br /&gt;
	Silent and majestic with wreaths of emerald green &amp;ndash;&lt;br /&gt;
	Their journey&amp;rsquo;s end and the Feet of the Supreme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Abhinabha&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


    

    &lt;span class=&quot;country&quot; x-autocompletetype=&quot;country&quot; autocomplete=&quot;country&quot;&gt;Netherlands&lt;/span&gt;    

